e given by the [[Valar|Vala]] [[Ulmo]] to [[Tuor]], who was in turn to deliver it to [[Turgon]], [[King of Gondolin]]. In the earlier writings it requested that Turgon sally forth to meet [[Morgoth]] in open battle, for the Valar would aid their victory, but if he would not go forth to war, then he must abandon Gondolin and lead his people down [[Sirion]] and seek back to [[Valinor]].<ref>{{LT2|III}}, pp. 161-162</ref><ref>{{SM|Q16}}, p. 142</ref>\n\nFor the edition of ''[[The Silmarillion]]'', [[Christopher Tolkien]] and [[Guy Gavriel Kay]] rewrote it to adjust it to the late version: Ulmo's warning announced that the doom of [[Gondolin]] was coming, suggesting that they seek to find a way to the [[Blessed Realm]].<ref>{{S|23}}</ref> Either way, Turgon did not heed this wise counsel, because of his pride, the love of his beautiful city and [[Maeglin]]'s advices.\n\n{{references}}\n{{gondolin}}\n\n[[Category:First Age]]\n[[Category:Oaths and prophecies]]"}}}